title: MENU ITEM - EL PINANGAT
creator: Savier Rolan B. Moya
description: Named EL PINANGAT and priced at P150 for two pieces. Pinangat or Pinangat na isda is a dish originating from the region of Bicol. Its main ingredients are fish, coconut milk, taro leaves, and hot chili peppers.
subject: MENU ITEM
location: 28 Cadig, La Loma, Quezon City, Metro Manila

title: MENU ITEM - EL DANGGIT
creator: Savier Rolan B. Moya
description: Named EL DANGGIT and priced at P150 for 100 grams. Danggit is a salted and sun-dried rabbitfish. The fish are usually split open, salted, and left to dry under the sun. This dish is also a popular breakfast food often eaten with eggs and rice alongside spicy vinegar as a dipping sauce.
subject: MENU ITEM
location: 28 Cadig, La Loma, Quezon City, Metro Manila

title: MENU ITEM - EL PUSIT
creator: Savier Rolan B. Moya
description: Named EL PUSIT and priced at P180 for 100 grams. Dried Pusit is a cleaned and sun-dried squid. It is prepared the same way as the Danggit.
subject: MENU ITEM
location: 28 Cadig, La Loma, Quezon City, Metro Manila

title: MENU ITEM - EL LUMPIANG LAING
creator: Savier Rolan B. Moya
description: Named EL LUMPIANG LAING and priced at P140. It is prepared by rolling laing in lumpia wrappers. It is then deep fried to achieve a crispy texture. Best served with spicy vinegar.
subject: MENU ITEM
location: 28 Cadig, La Loma, Quezon City, Metro Manila
